==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uxorious
<hw>Ux*o"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>uxorius</ets>, fr. <ets>uxor</ets> a wife.]</ety> <def>Excessively
fond of, or submissive to, a wife; being a dependent husband.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Uxorious</xex> magistrates.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How wouldst thou insult,⟦br⟧
When I must live <qex>uxorious</qex> to thy will⟦br⟧
In perfect thraldom!</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ux*o"ri*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ux*o"ri*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uzema</ent>⟦br⟧
